text:
can you please have a look at this?

&lt;
(<https://elmlang.slack.com/archives/C0CJ3SBBM/p1551346567012100?thread_ts=1551346142.009900&amp;cid=C0CJ3SBBM>)&gt;

Hi, I would like some help with Http requests, tasks &amp; updates. I have a situation where in an update function I'd like to fetch some data, update the model and then navigate the another page. I struggling to understand if I can achieve this without multiple messages that all know what step of the process they are at. My incorrect first attempt was:
```
        EditUserResponse userUpload result -&gt;
            case result of
                Ok _ -&gt;
                    { model
                        | fullUser = RemoteData.NotAsked
                    }
                        ! [ Users.User.Tasks.fetchAllUsers
                                |&gt; Task.andThen
                                    (\users -&gt;
                                        Task.sequence
                                            [ Task.perform (MsgForUser &lt;&lt; AllUsersResponse) &lt;| Task.succeed users

                                            -- Navigate back to the ViewUser page 
                                            , Task.perform GoToUrl &lt;| Task.succeed &lt;| url &lt;| ViewUser userUpload.userId &lt;| UserD.urlSlug userUpload
                                            ]
                                    )
                          ]

                Err error -&gt;
                    model ! []
```
Not sure if that makes sense but I'd like to delay the `GoToUrl` navigation until I have the users data back from `fetchAllUsers`. Is such a thing possible or do I need to have intermediate messages to help handle the stages?
